  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve Sustainable WaSH through Income-Generating Activities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Within funding from the French Embassy (CDCS), Action Against Hunger proposes a soap making project within refugee camp to ensure that soap is affordable and always available within the camp. Action Against Hunger will provide 10 women groups of 20 members each (14 Refugee: 6 Host community) with ingredients necessary for making both liquid and bar soap. The women groups shall be trained on the process of soap making and on ways of independently obtaining the ingredients for soap making. The women shall also be trained on the marketing of products and financial literacy.</narrative>
  </description>
